The paper deals with computational tasks on a point set in $\Re^d$, which is a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of nearest-neighbor search is also a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for clustering and classification tasks. The paper also mentions the problem of clustering the point set, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) for image segmentation and object recognition.
